721651f-a.text:
Minetta Lane, north side, from but not including MacDougal Street, west to the intersection of Sixth Ave., and Carmine Street.
This lane will soon be modernised.
1923.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.

721650f-a.text:
Minetta Lane, from MacDougal Street, to the intersection of Sixth Ave. and Carmine Street, showing a modern paved street
with several new buildings.
About 1925.

721162f-a.text:
115, 117 Macdougal Street, at and adjoining the N.W. corner of Minetta Lane, south of West 3rd (formerly Amity) Street. No. 115 is (obviously) an old stable. Notice the beam proiecting over the tall upper window in the center. A pulley was fastened to this so that
bales of hay could be hoisted up into the hayloft.
May 23, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
